{"word":"ἀπόστολος","slug":"ἀπόστολος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπόστολος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀποστέλλω'><el>ἀποστέλλω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a messenger, ambassador, envoy</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a sacred messenger, an Apostle</i>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>= <a href='S:στόλος'><el>στόλος</el></a>, <i>a naval squadron</i> or <i>expedition</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}